---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Breadcrumb from '../../components/Breadcrumb.astro';
import Alert from '../../components/Alert.astro';
import Accordion from '../../components/Accordion.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="Troubleshooting: Forgotten Admin Password Recovery"
	description="Lost access to router or filtering software. Learn how to recover or reset admin credentials safely."
>
	<Breadcrumb />

	<div class="guide-container">
		<header class="guide-header">
			<div class="difficulty-badge intermediate">Intermediate</div>
			<h1>Forgotten Admin Password Recovery</h1>
			<p class="subtitle">
				Lost access to router or filtering software. Recover or reset admin credentials safely.
			</p>
			<div class="meta">
				<span>‚è±Ô∏è Time Required: 10-30 minutes</span>
				<span>üîß Difficulty: Intermediate</span>
			</div>
		</header>

		<Alert type="warning">
			<strong>Important:</strong> Some password recovery methods will reset ALL settings, not just the password.
			Be prepared to reconfigure filtering from scratch.
		</Alert>

		<section class="guide-section">
			<h2>Router Admin Password Recovery</h2>

			<div class="step">
				<h3><span class="step-number">1</span> Try Default Credentials First</h3>
				<p>If you never changed the password, it might still be the factory default:</p>

				<h4>Common Default Passwords:</h4>
				<ul>
					<li><strong>Username:</strong> admin | <strong>Password:</strong> admin</li>
					<li><strong>Username:</strong> admin | <strong>Password:</strong> password</li>
					<li><strong>Username:</strong> admin | <strong>Password:</strong> (blank/empty)</li>
					<li><strong>Username:</strong> administrator | <strong>Password:</strong> administrator</li>
				</ul>

				<h4>Find Your Router's Defaults:</h4>
				<ol>
					<li>Check the label on the bottom/back of your router</li>
					<li>Look in the router's manual (or download from manufacturer website)</li>
					<li>Visit <strong>RouterPasswords.com</strong> or <strong>DefaultPassword.com</strong></li>
					<li>Search Google for "[Your router model] default password"</li>
				</ol>

				<div class="info-box">
					<strong>Popular Router Defaults:</strong>
					<ul>
						<li><strong>Netgear:</strong> admin / password</li>
						<li><strong>TP-Link:</strong> admin / admin</li>
						<li><strong>Linksys:</strong> admin / admin (or blank)</li>
						<li><strong>ASUS:</strong> admin / admin</li>
						<li><strong>D-Link:</strong> admin / (blank)</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
			</div>

			<div class="step">
				<h3><span class="step-number">2</span> Check Common Password Storage Locations</h3>
				<p>Before resetting, check if you saved the password somewhere:</p>
				<ul>
					<li>Browser password manager (check saved passwords)</li>
					<li>Password manager app (1Password, LastPass, Bitwarden)</li>
					<li>Sticky note on router or nearby</li>
					<li>Family shared password document</li>
					<li>Router setup documentation from ISP</li>
					<li>Email search for "router password" or "WiFi setup"</li>
				</ul>
			</div>

			<div class="step">
				<h3><span class="step-number">3</span> Perform a Factory Reset</h3>
				<p>If defaults don't work and password is truly lost, reset the router:</p>

				<Alert type="error">
					<strong>Warning:</strong> This erases ALL router settings:
					<ul>
						<li>WiFi network name and password</li>
						<li>DNS filtering settings</li>
						<li>Port forwarding rules</li>
						<li>Parental controls</li>
						<li>Guest network configuration</li>
					</ul>
					<p>You'll need to reconfigure everything from scratch. Write down current WiFi credentials first!</p>
				</Alert>

				<h4>How to Factory Reset Most Routers:</h4>
				<ol>
					<li>Locate the <strong>Reset button</strong> on the router (usually recessed, requires paperclip)</li>
					<li>While router is powered ON, press and hold Reset button</li>
					<li>Hold for <strong>10-30 seconds</strong> (LED lights will usually flash)</li>
					<li>Release button when lights flash or after 30 seconds</li>
					<li>Wait 2-3 minutes for router to fully restart</li>
					<li>Router will now accept factory default credentials</li>
				</ol>

				<h4>Brand-Specific Reset Instructions:</h4>

				<strong>Netgear:</strong>
				<ol>
					<li>Press and hold Reset button for 7 seconds</li>
					<li>Power LED will blink amber</li>
					<li>Release when LED turns white</li>
				</ol>

				<strong>TP-Link:</strong>
				<ol>
					<li>Hold Reset button for 10 seconds while powered on</li>
					<li>All LEDs will turn off and back on</li>
					<li>Release button</li>
				</ol>

				<strong>ASUS:</strong>
				<ol>
					<li>Hold Reset button for 5-10 seconds</li>
					<li>Power LED will flash slowly</li>
					<li>Release when LED stops flashing</li>
				</ol>

				<strong>Linksys:</strong>
				<ol>
					<li>Hold Reset button for 10 seconds</li>
					<li>Power light will flash</li>
					<li>Release and wait for restart</li>
				</ol>
			</div>

			<div class="step">
				<h3><span class="step-number">4</span> Reconfigure After Reset</h3>
				<p>Once reset, you must set everything up again:</p>

				<h4>Immediate Steps:</h4>
				<ol>
					<li>Connect to router using Ethernet cable or default WiFi</li>
					<li>Access router admin (usually 192.168.1.1 or 192.168.0.1)</li>
					<li>Log in with factory default credentials</li>
					<li><strong>IMMEDIATELY change admin password</strong> (and write it down!)</li>
					<li>Change WiFi network name and password</li>
				</ol>

				<h4>Restore Filtering:</h4>
				<ol>
					<li>Configure DNS filtering (see our <a href="/guides/dns-filtering">DNS filtering guide</a>)</li>
					<li>Re-enable parental controls</li>
					<li>Set up guest network if needed</li>
					<li>Configure any other security settings</li>
				</ol>

				<Alert type="info">
					<strong>Pro Tip:</strong> Take screenshots of all important router settings so you have a backup if this happens again.
				</Alert>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="guide-section">
			<h2>Filtering Software Password Recovery</h2>

			<div class="accordion-list">
				<Accordion title="OpenDNS Account" defaultOpen={true}>
					<h4>Forgot Password:</h4>
					<ol>
						<li>Go to <strong>dashboard.opendns.com</strong></li>
						<li>Click <strong>"Forgot Password?"</strong></li>
						<li>Enter your email address</li>
						<li>Check email for password reset link</li>
						<li>Create new password</li>
					</ol>

					<h4>Forgot Email:</h4>
					<ul>
						<li>Check browser auto-fill when visiting dashboard</li>
						<li>Search email for "OpenDNS" to find account confirmation</li>
						<li>If truly lost, create a new account and reconfigure DNS settings</li>
					</ul>
				</Accordion>

				<Accordion title="CleanBrowsing Account">
					<h4>Free Service:</h4>
					<p>No account required for free DNS filtering. Just use the DNS servers.</p>

					<h4>Paid Service:</h4>
					<ol>
						<li>Go to <strong>cleanbrowsing.org/login</strong></li>
						<li>Click <strong>"Forgot your password?"</strong></li>
						<li>Enter registered email</li>
						<li>Follow email instructions to reset</li>
					</ol>
				</Accordion>

				<Accordion title="Qustodio">
					<h4>Parent Account Recovery:</h4>
					<ol>
						<li>Visit <strong>family.qustodio.com</strong></li>
						<li>Click <strong>"Forgot password?"</strong></li>
						<li>Enter your email address</li>
						<li>Check email for reset link (check spam folder)</li>
						<li>Set new password</li>
					</ol>

					<h4>Cannot Remove from Device:</h4>
					<p>If you can't log into Qustodio to uninstall it:</p>
					<ol>
						<li>Contact Qustodio support with proof of device ownership</li>
						<li>They can reset your account or provide removal instructions</li>
						<li>Last resort: Factory reset device (nuclear option)</li>
					</ol>
				</Accordion>

				<Accordion title="Net Nanny">
					<h4>Account Recovery:</h4>
					<ol>
						<li>Go to <strong>admin.netnanny.com</strong></li>
						<li>Click <strong>"Forgot Password"</strong></li>
						<li>Enter email and follow instructions</li>
					</ol>

					<h4>Lost Access Completely:</h4>
					<ol>
						<li>Contact Net Nanny support: 1-800-485-3011</li>
						<li>Provide proof of purchase</li>
						<li>They can reset your account</li>
					</ol>
				</Accordion>

				<Accordion title="Bark">
					<h4>Parent App Password Reset:</h4>
					<ol>
						<li>Open Bark parent app</li>
						<li>Tap <strong>"Forgot password?"</strong> on login screen</li>
						<li>Enter email address</li>
						<li>Check email for code</li>
						<li>Enter code and set new password</li>
					</ol>

					<h4>Cannot Access Email:</h4>
					<ol>
						<li>Contact Bark support via website</li>
						<li>Verify identity with billing information</li>
						<li>They can update email or reset account</li>
					</ol>
				</Accordion>

				<Accordion title="Circle by Disney">
					<h4>App Password Reset:</h4>
					<ol>
						<li>Open Circle app</li>
						<li>Login screen ‚Üí <strong>"Forgot Password?"</strong></li>
						<li>Enter email and follow instructions</li>
					</ol>

					<h4>Physical Device Reset:</h4>
					<p>If you have the physical Circle device:</p>
					<ol>
						<li>Press and hold button on Circle device for 10 seconds</li>
						<li>LED will flash red</li>
						<li>Device resets to factory settings</li>
						<li>Reconfigure in app</li>
					</ol>
				</Accordion>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="guide-section">
			<h2>Device-Level Controls Password Recovery</h2>

			<div class="accordion-list">
				<Accordion title="iOS Screen Time Passcode">
					<h4>Forgot Screen Time Passcode:</h4>

					<strong>iOS 13.4 or Later:</strong>
					<ol>
						<li>Settings ‚Üí Screen Time</li>
						<li>Tap <strong>"Change Screen Time Passcode"</strong></li>
						<li>Tap again to confirm</li>
						<li>Select <strong>"Forgot Passcode?"</strong></li>
						<li>Enter Apple ID and password used to set up Screen Time</li>
						<li>Create new Screen Time passcode</li>
					</ol>

					<strong>Older iOS Versions:</strong>
					<p>No recovery option available. Must factory reset device:</p>
					<ol>
						<li>Back up device to iCloud or computer first</li>
						<li>Settings ‚Üí General ‚Üí Transfer or Reset iPhone</li>
						<li>Erase All Content and Settings</li>
						<li>Set up as new device or restore backup</li>
						<li>Screen Time restrictions will be removed</li>
					</ol>

					<Alert type="warning">
						Factory reset is drastic. Try Apple Support first‚Äîthey may be able to help verify identity and reset.
					</Alert>
				</Accordion>

				<Accordion title="Android Family Link">
					<h4>Parent Account Password:</h4>
					<ol>
						<li>Visit <strong>accounts.google.com</strong></li>
						<li>Click <strong>"Forgot password?"</strong></li>
						<li>Follow Google account recovery process</li>
						<li>Verify identity with phone number or recovery email</li>
					</ol>

					<h4>Cannot Remove Family Link:</h4>
					<p>If parent account is lost and child device is locked:</p>
					<ol>
						<li>Factory reset is the only option</li>
						<li>Power off device</li>
						<li>Boot into recovery mode (varies by device, usually Volume Down + Power)</li>
						<li>Select "Wipe data/factory reset"</li>
						<li>Device will be completely wiped</li>
					</ol>
				</Accordion>

				<Accordion title="Windows Family Safety">
					<h4>Microsoft Account Recovery:</h4>
					<ol>
						<li>Go to <strong>account.microsoft.com</strong></li>
						<li>Click <strong>"Sign in"</strong> then <strong>"Forgot password?"</strong></li>
						<li>Enter email/phone/Skype name</li>
						<li>Verify identity (security code to email/phone)</li>
						<li>Create new password</li>
					</ol>

					<h4>Child Account Locked:</h4>
					<p>If you can't remove Family Safety from child's Windows account:</p>
					<ol>
						<li>Boot into Safe Mode (restart, hold Shift, Troubleshoot ‚Üí Advanced ‚Üí Startup Settings ‚Üí Safe Mode)</li>
						<li>Log in as local administrator</li>
						<li>Remove child from family via Settings ‚Üí Accounts ‚Üí Family</li>
						<li>Or create new local admin account and migrate data</li>
					</ol>
				</Accordion>

				<Accordion title="macOS Screen Time">
					<h4>Recovery Process:</h4>
					<p>Similar to iOS, but slightly different:</p>
					<ol>
						<li>System Settings (or Preferences) ‚Üí Screen Time</li>
						<li>Click lock icon, try to change passcode</li>
						<li><strong>"Forgot Passcode?"</strong></li>
						<li>Enter Apple ID credentials</li>
						<li>Reset passcode</li>
					</ol>

					<h4>If Apple ID Method Fails:</h4>
					<ol>
						<li>Boot into Recovery Mode (restart, hold Cmd+R)</li>
						<li>Utilities ‚Üí Terminal</li>
						<li>Type: <code>resetpassword</code></li>
						<li>Select user account</li>
						<li>Option to reset Screen Time passcode appears</li>
					</ol>
				</Accordion>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="guide-section">
			<h2>Prevention: Never Lose Passwords Again</h2>

			<h3>Use a Password Manager</h3>
			<p>Store all filtering/router passwords securely:</p>
			<ul>
				<li><strong>1Password:</strong> $2.99/month, excellent family sharing</li>
				<li><strong>Bitwarden:</strong> Free (premium $10/year), open source</li>
				<li><strong>LastPass:</strong> Free for single device, premium for families</li>
				<li><strong>Apple Keychain:</strong> Free, built into Apple devices</li>
				<li><strong>Google Password Manager:</strong> Free, built into Chrome</li>
			</ul>

			<h3>Physical Backup</h3>
			<ul class="checklist">
				<li>Write passwords in a physical notebook kept in secure location</li>
				<li>Label clearly: "Router Admin," "OpenDNS Account," etc.</li>
				<li>Store in locked drawer or safe</li>
				<li>Update whenever passwords change</li>
			</ul>

			<h3>Digital Backup (Encrypted)</h3>
			<ul class="checklist">
				<li>Create a secure document with all credentials</li>
				<li>Encrypt with password or store in password manager</li>
				<li>Include: Router admin, filtering accounts, device passcodes</li>
				<li>Keep backup copy in secure cloud storage</li>
			</ul>

			<h3>Family Password Sharing</h3>
			<ul class="checklist">
				<li>Share critical passwords with spouse/co-parent</li>
				<li>Use password manager family sharing feature</li>
				<li>Ensures redundancy if one parent forgets</li>
				<li>Keep separate from kids' access</li>
			</ul>

			<h3>Documentation</h3>
			<ul class="checklist">
				<li>Take screenshots of all router settings</li>
				<li>Document DNS server addresses used</li>
				<li>Write down WiFi credentials</li>
				<li>Store in password manager "Secure Notes" section</li>
			</ul>

			<Alert type="success">
				<strong>Best Practice:</strong> Store router admin password in two locations‚Äîpassword manager + written note in locked drawer.
			</Alert>
		</section>

		<section class="guide-section">
			<h2>When to Contact Support</h2>
			<p>Some situations require manufacturer assistance:</p>

			<h3>Contact Router Manufacturer If:</h3>
			<ul>
				<li>Factory reset didn't work (button may be broken)</li>
				<li>Default credentials don't work after reset</li>
				<li>Router is from ISP and reset is disabled</li>
				<li>Need to preserve complex configuration while resetting password</li>
			</ul>

			<h3>Contact Filtering Service If:</h3>
			<ul>
				<li>Account recovery emails aren't arriving</li>
				<li>Don't have access to registered email anymore</li>
				<li>Billing information available to verify identity</li>
				<li>Software is locked and cannot be removed</li>
			</ul>

			<h3>Contact Device Manufacturer (Apple/Google/Microsoft) If:</h3>
			<ul>
				<li>Account recovery methods aren't working</li>
				<li>Device is locked with parental controls</li>
				<li>Can prove device ownership</li>
				<li>Activation lock or FRP (Factory Reset Protection) is preventing access</li>
			</ul>

			<div class="info-box">
				<strong>Support Resources:</strong>
				<ul>
					<li><strong>Apple Support:</strong> 1-800-275-2273 or support.apple.com</li>
					<li><strong>Google Support:</strong> support.google.com (no phone support for consumer accounts)</li>
					<li><strong>Microsoft Support:</strong> 1-800-642-7676 or support.microsoft.com</li>
				</ul>
			</div>
		</section>

		<div class="related-guides">
			<h2>Related Guides</h2>
			<div class="related-grid">
				<a href="/guides/router-config" class="related-card">
					<h3>Router Configuration</h3>
					<p>Complete router setup guide</p>
				</a>
				<a href="/guides/dns-filtering" class="related-card">
					<h3>DNS Filtering Setup</h3>
					<p>Reconfigure DNS filtering after reset</p>
				</a>
				<a href="/troubleshooting/dns-not-working" class="related-card">
					<h3>DNS Not Working</h3>
					<p>Verify filtering is working correctly</p>
				</a>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</Layout>

